We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct:

In case of use of funds to COVID-19 PPA, the MPDC to determine COVID-19 PPAs that could be funded from the savings from implementation of NGA funded projects;

The Municipal Budget Officer to ensure that budgeting guidelines are followed such as inclusion of the PPAs in the Annual Investment Program and Annual Budget of the LGU through enactment of Appropriation Ordinance; 

In case of non-usage of the fund, the Municipal Accountant to prepare the Disbursement Voucher for remittance of the funds from savings of implementation to National Treasury, and thereafter, the Municipal Treasurer to cause the preparation and release of checks.

The Municipal Engineer to submit the documents required by the Department of Health and Department of Agriculture for the receipt of the remaining balance. Thereafter, to immediately settle the amounts due to contractor.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct:
The Municipal Accountant to furnish documents in support of the duly established/recognized Accounts Payable, otherwise, derecognize the amount of ₱133,517.49 in the books of the LGU;
The Municipal Accountant to initiate the request for the reversal of unliquidated balances of Accounts Payable and make an entry for the reversion of the balance to the General Fund and include such amount in funding additional PPAs;
The Municipal Treasurer to cause the immediate payment of accumulated aids to barangay after the preparation of the by the Municipal Accountant of Disbursement Voucher.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct:
In case of use of funds to COVID-19 PPA:
The MPDC to determine COVID-19 PPAs that could be funded from the savings from implementation of NGA funded projects;
The Municipal Budget Officer to ensure that budgeting guidelines are followed such as inclusion of the PPAs in the Annual Investment Program and Annual Budget of the LGU through enactment of Appropriation Ordinance;
In case of non-usage of fund, the Municipal Accountant to prepare the Disbursement Voucher for remittance of the funds from savings of implementation to National Treasury, thereafter, the Municipal Treasurer to cause the preparation and release of checks.
The Municipal Engineer to submit the documents required by the Department of Health and Department of Agriculture for the receipt of remaining balance. Thereafter, to immediately settle the amounts due to contractor.

